SPREAD Operator -- ( ... )
allows an iterable such as an array or string to be expanded into seperate elements.

let numbers = [ 1 , 2 , 3 , 4 , 5 ];
let max = Math.max(numbers) -- wrong as it cannot iterate to find the max no.
so we use the spread operator -- max = Math.max( ...numbers );

for strings too it can be used -- let name = "Ronit";
let letters = [...name]; -- unpacks the string into seperate elements.
console.log(letters);

We can join them again by using the join method --
letters = [...name].join("-");

let fruits = ["apples","oranges","guavas"];
let newfruits = [...fruits]; -- Shallow copy of array fruits.
We can also join diffn arrays while copying like  -- 
let newfruits = [...fruits, ...vegetables , "eggs" , "milk"];

REST parameters --
rest parameters = (...rest) allow a function work with a variable number of arguments by bundling them into an array.
-- Bundles seperate elements into an array

const food1 ="Pizza";
const food2 ="Burger";
const food3 = "Sushi";
const food4 ="Ramen";

function  openFridge(...foods){ // accepts a number of arguments and combine them into an array -- foods
	console.log(foods);
}

openFridge(food1,foods,food3,food4);

We use rest parameters to combine parameters and Spread operator to seperate individual elements from the array.
Rest parameters also help in combining strings into one single string.

function fullname(...strings){
	return strings.join(" ");
}
console.log(fullname("Mr.", "Ronit" , "Dey"));

